CatDescriptText: Mrs. Francis Pettigrew, 2838 Centre Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 25, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that business and employment are as good as the Eisenhower administration declares that it is?" answer reads: "No, I really don't think so. I could be prejudiced a little, because I've just been laid off because of a work shortage at the Fisher Scientific Laboratory."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Frances Pettigrew wearing light colored hat with flower and dark coat with flower on left lapel, holding bag and handbag, standing on sidewalk with trees and automobiles in background
